Rating: 4
Please add some pork ribs, beef stock and remove the turnips. Start the soup by frying the chopped onion and garlic in olive oil, then add the chopped meats until sealed. Then add the vegetables, the stock and the seasoning.Simmer for 2- 3 hrs. This is the real portuguese "stone" soup. By the way, this soup has its origin in an ancient story: a pilgrim knocked at a farmer's door and asked for food but the farmer said no; the pilgrim then asked the farmer just for some water and a pot so that he could make some soup with the stone he had in his pouch; the farmer provided the water..but was curious about what kind of a soup resulted from water and a stone; then the pilgrim asked the farmer for 1 potato, just to add flavour, and the farmer gave him 1 potato.. and remained curious; then the pilgrim asked the farmer for 1 small carrot, just to add some colour; and like this... the pilgrim obtained all the ingredients; by now, the soup smelled fantastic; when finished, the pilgrim offered the farmer some soup, which was obviously delicious with so many ingredients; the pilgrim thanked the farmer, removed the stone from the pot, ... and started a new journey.

